      "content": "Wait, there a couple of issues with your code. First, `run_test` is using `n_runs` but it's not defined inside that function, so it's going to throw a NameError unless it's a global, which is messy. \n\nAlso, your logic for detecting flakiness is a bit weird: `if len(set(results)) > 1 or not all(results):`. If a test is perfectly stable but always returns `False`, `not all(results)` will be `True`, and your detector will flag it as flaky. That's definitely not what I want—a stable test that returns `False` is just a stable failing test, not a flaky one.\n\nCan you fix the scope error and refine the logic so it only returns `True` if the results actually vary? I need it to be robust.",
      "source": "evaluator"
